TWO suspected illegal miners were arrested while the third one was shot dead during a shoot-out with cops on Thursday, 19 January. The police were patrolling when they noticed a group of suspects, illegally mining gold-bearing soil, on a farm near Selwane village, Limpopo. Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said they approached the suspects but one opened fire on cops, who retaliated, fatally wounding him. “Police managed to arrest two suspects and recover one firearm, allegedly belonging to the deceased,” Mojapelo said. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments The arrested suspects, aged 23 and 43, were charged with illegal mining and contravention of the Immigration Act, and will appear in the Lulekani Magistrates Court soon.